Package it.polimi.ingsw.client

Class ActionInputParser

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.client.ActionInputParser
All Implemented Interfaces:
PropertyChangeListener, EventListener
public class ActionInputParser extends Object implements PropertyChangeListener
ActionInputParser receives an action request from the UserInterface during his turn. The request is parsed in order to check if all parameters are present: if so the action is passed to the ActionMessageConstructor, otherwise the UserInterface and the TurnHandler are notified about the error.

  • Constructor Details

    • ActionInputParser

      public ActionInputParser(PropertyChangeListener messageConstructor, TurnHandler turnHandler, UserInterface userInterface, ModelView modelView)
      Construct a new instance of ActionInputParser. The new object will be bound with the specified PropertyChangeListener (the MessageConstructor that will construct the message that will be sent to the server), the specified TurnHandler, the specified UserInterface that will be notified about errors and the specified ModelView that will be used to recognise errors.
      Parameters:
      messageConstructor - the listener on which correct actions will be passed
      turnHandler - the turn handler of the client
      userInterface - the user interface of the client
      modelView - the model view of the client
